text: This is very random but I’m leaving for Wisconsin this week and I need to ship back quite a few things from my dad’s house that sold. (My sister said there are a lot of boxes and random things). Does anyone know of a cheap way to ship that much stuff across country? It doesn’t matter how slowly it gets to me—just trying to find the most economic way to do it. Any insight is appreciated :smile:

<@U1HKQRLMR> The details are a bit fuzzy as it has been awhile since I’ve shipped stuff across the country, but I believe if you go through the USPS and you ship stuff in pretty big boxes, that you can get a bit of a deal. I would go there and inquire. Also, if you have any books, cds, papers, etc. you can send those media mail at a discounted rate.
Thank you!
For anyone else, I've heard good things about uShip
I’m definitely going to check that one out :smile:

<!channel> On a similar note, has anyone found any good companies to ship large quantities of stuff from abroad to the US? I have about 100 lbs of stuff I need shipped from the UK to the US.

I'm not sure about specific companies, but when my parents had to ship stuff from the US to Japan, they found that filling a pallet and shipping stuff as freight was far cheaper than any other option.

and <@U1HKQRLMR> I think when i researched this in the past, amtrak doesn't serve all markets, so i'd check to make sure you can do wisconsin -> portland.  greyhound is a great option for large items like furniture.  Also, you can save a bunch by labeling boxes as media mail with USPS - it's how i moved here from NYC for only $200 :grin:
<@U243UT96G> Thanks! If you do the media option though, don’t you have to pack the tops with books or something in case they open them?
yes, that's what I did - as long as the box "feels" like it could be books, i think you're ok.
Alrighty. Idk if there are that many books in the pile. But I’ll look into all the options.
the postal worker that was helping me that day gave me the worst stink eye ever though... i had boxes spilling out for a block on atlantic avenue
Whoops haha
I also moved cross-country via USPS. No furniture, but even with boxes that were not media mail, it was pretty inexpensive to ship at the lowest rate.
